translated: Lundström, David Gunnar Davids-son, district judge, military judge, Kalmar, b. 2/6/85 in Örgryte, Gothenburg and Bohus County, son of merchant David L. and Hilda Prytz. Married on the 14th to Ragnhild Berndtson. Children: Gunvor, born in 1915, gymnastics director, married to Lieutenant Lennart von Bahr in Stockholm, Bengt David Fredrik Gunnarsson, born in 1916, law graduate, welfare officer in Hälsingborg, Birgit, born in 1918, clerk at Skandinaviska Enskilda Banken in Stockholm, married to clerk at the same bank, Sten Aprdh, Karin, born in 1918, clerk at A-B Flygtjänst in Stockholm. Law graduate from Lund in 1914. District judge in Nordmarks district court from 1932, in N. Möre and Strands district court from 1941, military judge at Kalmar airbase from 1942. Captain in reserve from 1925. Chairman of the temperance movement in Kalmar. Awarded RNO, CBFSM, Kalm. bef.utb. -förb. GM, Värml. skytteförb. SM, Värml. 1. landst. -förb. SM, and Gold Shooting Medal.
